
    YouTube entertainer Moshe Ndiki is the new face of the reality dating show Uyang’thanda Na?The TV presenter, actor and now musician, will play Cupid as the host of the second season of the show, starting tonight at 8pm.Lonely hopefuls confess their love to their secret crushes on the dating show.Each episode concludes with a verdict from the admired other, when they get to answer the very important question: “Uyang’thanda Na?”Moshe told Daily Sun he always wanted to be part of show and was grateful for the opportunity.“It feels amazing to be part of such a wonderful show.”“I auditioned like any other presenter but Lady Luck was on my side and I got the job.”Moshe rose to fame when he became a social media sensation, and his hilarious outbursts, wild dress sense and candid behaviour will certainly bring a lighter side to the show.He promised viewers fun, entertainment and good television.Moshe expressed his delight at joining the show.“I believe in love and reckon it is something worth fighting for.“Fight for it hard and always give love just one more chance,” he said. Sphumelele Sibeko, head of reality content on M-Net local entertainment channels, said Moshe’s engagement with hopefuls on the show is effortless and will certainly keep viewers intrigued.“We look forward to having him on Uyang’thanda Na? and trust his sparkling personality will come through.”The show is produced by Parental Advisory Productions.In 2016, Moshe was a guest continuity presenter on MTV Africa for five days.Uyang’thanda Na? returns to Mzansi Magic (DStv channel 161) tonight at 8pm.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsv-1_yetnnY3ppq9Jbq3JuVtjGnfrGiHPdVxsVlJmQYSl3ojnvBScCW6kn-bAly8tpnhqnBe5Gfdzsll36N48sV4C4ylfZNZdqUWnHimEpnwXpv2QYZnArUaA5Z_rWxobPzohYtYhglldHhdJRvtp_B0Tchip5cFFrxK8C9Go4